778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uturrun.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Turrun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(3/15/01 12:22:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=199.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Bard in Freeport</span><hr size=1> I finally got to dubious with the Freeport militia last night and decided to try giving the bard money to help faction with the Knights of Truth.<br><br>I was having trouble finding anyone to cast wolform, so decided to gamble.  What I discovered was a way to complete the quest without need wolform!<br><br>When you arrive at the tavern in East Freeport, the bard inside is most likely still KOS.  This is why wolform was recommended.  I found that I could go behind and around the tavern to a second entrance.  From there, I was able to sneak inside, hugging the wall to my left and move around the tavern behind the bard without getting in his line of sight.  <br><br>Be aware that this is very tricky because you will be right on the edge of his aggro radius.  But if you can't find wolform, it is doable.  Took me about 300gp to get to dubious with him and the Knights. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ugoldmundtargari.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goldmund TargaRi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(3/15/01 1:22:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=199.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Big secret to getting free druid buffs...</span><hr size=1> This might belong in a separate thread, but several people have been asking on the going rate for wolfform, so here goes:<br><br>I've played a druid mostly un-anon to 53, so I consider myself an expert when it comes to buff begging :P  Here are some simple guidelines for free buffs:<br><br>1) Be right in front of the druid.  Don't send a tell to the first name on a /who druid list and expect them to find you or wait for you to find them.<br><br>2) Use their name.  If I'm sitting somewhere resting, chances are I'm busy in /tells or /gu, and if there are several people around it's really easy to ignore the /says.  Using a name is also just the polite thing to do.<br><br>3) Don't abbreviate.  The quickest way to get ignored is to utter the infamous "sow plz".  If you can't be bothered to spend the extra 5 seconds it takes to type out complete words, I can't be bothered to cast a spell.  <br><br>4) There is no step 4.  If you do the above 3 things you will be guaranteed a buff 99% of the time.  <br><br>I have *never* refused to buff someone that asked politely.  Conversely, my monk and paladin have never been turned down when I asked in a polite manner.  Chances are the druid will be so shocked to see a well-formed, polite request that you'll get a full buff package.   <p>--<BR><a href=http://www.alltel.net/~mr81645/Gold_Image/goldmundmap.htm>Goldmund Targa`Ri</a> ~ Wanderer of the 53rd Season<BR>Moro - 33rd Iksar Monk<BR>Jorah Mormont - 24th Human Paladin<BR>Ascension of the Damned ~ Quellious</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uxodai.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xodai</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(3/16/01 7:28:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=199.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> freeport faction</span><hr size=1> First of all.. great guide Anezka!!<br><br>Just wanted to add my 2cp on getting freeport faction.  I'm an Iksar Monk and I did this at about level 33.  Here's how I did it:<br><br>First I tried doing the Janum and Rebby quest with my 17 ranger, but I got bored really fast with all that running back and forth so I quit after getting about 40 whiskers.. I didn't bother with the note because I don't have 2 computers and accounts.  Doing this didn't seem to get me anywhere.  So then I killed Orcs at orc 1 in EC, where the most orcs pop.. lost of people tried to tell me WC was better, but it's not.  As I killed orcs I made sure to gather up as many deathfist slashed belts and orc pawn scalps as I could.  Then I got wolf form and turned in about 6 bags of belts to the militia captain... this hurt my north freeport faction but that's easy to get back...  and it got me dubious to the guards in West and East freeport.  I was still scowled at by the ashen order, so I killed more orcs until wolf form got me to high amiable.  Then I did the white headband quest about 60-80 times.  Pretty easy considering all the items for it can be bought of vendors or newbies in west freeport.  After that boom I'm looked upon warmly by the ashen order and the guards in North freeport are dubious so I can bank.  <br><br>Good luck fellow monkeys.<br><br>Xodai<br>Swiftail Monk of the 40th Kata<br>Sacred Legends - E'ci<br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.sacredlegends.com">www.sacredlegends.com</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=anezka>Anezka</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www3.sympatico.ca/pratte1/Icone.bmp BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Disciple</span><br>  Posts: 171<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(3/29/01 9:40:25 am)