uffs.  kudos<br><br>Now my 2cp on Freeport Militia faction.<br>Killing Lucan 3 times will make your faction max'd bottom and unrecoverable.  I am a Freeport Monk, and have done most of the Freeport quest, and had both my Knight's and Militia factions very high. (kindly/warmly don't remember for sure)<br>The only Freeport guards I have ever killed were Lucan.  We hail-pulled him to kill him and never had an add.<br>I have been told that a GM confirmed that some factions can become unrecoverable, and that Lucan is one of them. <p><html><head><title></title></head><body><p align="center"><font color="#FF0000"><b><blink>Grazzt</blink></b></font></p><p align="center">(formerly Takish'Hiz)</p><p align="center">Monk of the Ashen Order</p><p align="center">Faithful of Quellious</p><p align="center"><em>"I must not fear. Fear is themind-killer. Fear is the little-death that brings totalobliteration. I will face my fear. I will permit it to pass overme. And when it has gone past I will turn the inner eye to seeits path. where the fear has gone there will be nothing. Only Iwill remain."</em></p></body></html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uzinj.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zinj</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 1209<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(4/18/01 6:49:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=199.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Factions...</span><hr size=1> araladium<br>    Monk<br>    posts: 1<br>    (4/16/01 10:12:18 am)<br>    Reply | Edit | Del All<br>                      Qeynos faction Non Kos in 7 hours or less <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>                      Just wanted to post that I spent about 7 hours total in BlackBurrow killing all the<br>                      gnolls I could find.<br><br>                      I am dubious to the monks atm, but am indifferent to the guards due to the gnoll<br>                      fang quest (guard captain in arena area). However, working faction in this manner<br>                      will leave you kos to the Corrupt guards and the bards. <br><br>                      For you iksar monks who want to do the ROTLC quest, be careful after your faction<br>                      is high enough with the monks to do this quest. There is a yellow con SK corrupt<br>                      guard there who HT's for 1000+ hps of damage.<br><br>                      Currently my dubious faction will not let me complete the monk quests, but I am<br>                      returning to BB to finish my faction work. One other note. I am amiable to the<br>                      merchants so they are a lot more forgiving than those damn human monks...hehe <br><br>                      Taeryn Sharptooth--(Taeryn@hotmail.com)<br>                      48 monk<br>                      Araladium<br>                      51 elementalist<br>                      Shining Alliance<br>                      Prexus Server<br>    guice666  <br>    Monk<br>    posts: 13<br>    (4/17/01 9:35:50 pm)<br>    Reply | Edit | Del<br>                      Re: Qeynos faction Non Kos in 7 hours or less <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>                      i would like to add to this. I have gotten nonKoS to the Steel Warriors and have<br>                      been able to run the Gnoll Fang quest too.<br><br>                      There are many factions within Qeynos, and it really sucks ( alot of high lvl KoS<br>                  