it more complicated. There is a lvl 50+ druid that likes to hang out<br>                      on the docs and in the tavern you have to turn in stones into.<br>                      Make sure you have a friend ( or alt char ) that can invis your through the run from<br>                      the arena to the one tavern ( I forget the name of it .. sorry ).<br>                      This quest will start raising your Pally and Cleric faction. So far, I have gotten myself<br>                      to threatening with them ( turned in 82 teeth and the 82 moonstones - get one<br>                      stone per tooth turned in ).<br>                      Another way to raise your faction is to use sneak and a friend to hail on the loud<br>                      mouth lvl5 cleric guy that leaves Qeynos at night. He wonders into the newbie area<br>                      and giving him 2 bone chips or 2 gold will result in a faction adjustment and a free<br>                      heal. Note: cause he gives you a heal, he *will* turn to you ( if you are high enoug,<br>                      he won't agro ). When he turns, he will see you, and you can't complete the quest<br>                      unless you use sneak. This where a friend to hail him comes into play. Hailing him will<br>                      cause him to turn towards the one that'd hailing.<br><br>                      Anyway, this is so far all that I've figured out about Qeynos. I still hadn't figured out<br>                      a way to raise my CircleofThree faction, atleast a way for an Iksar to do it. I'm still<br>                      playing with that. The druid iin SQ, I have NO clue what faction he's on sadly. Not<br>                      on JaggedPineTreefolk like the other karana druids. Still investigating him.<br><br>                      Oh, enough gnolls, and you will be able to safely gate to the karana's w/out the<br>                      need for invis  <br><br>             