h its greyed out) after turning in all the hides and moving. You cant carry enough hides in one shot to become non kos. You will get a lot of black wolf armor, feel free to sell it, or twink a barb rogue with a sleek black look. (Be warned every looser in the world will think your twinked out in this stuff called raven scale and feel the need to call you names.. the armor is kinda crappy in reality) After a while you will be non kos to the bank rogues.<br><br>The first part should take care of the guys in FV as well, thats the only town I havent done so personally I do not know.<br><br>-<br><br>I noticed you mentioned your only interested in doing the good aligned towns. Its mostly easy to get into Erudin by killing Elial Broks at the dock in Toxx. If you kill him 60 times, then take his 60 drops of 'bones' to Markus Jaevins by useing a invis potion and sneak you will end up being non kos to everybody in the place except the Qellous clerics. (You will be threatening)<br><br>You can then do the 'inert potion quest' which raises Coalition of Trade Folk Ill, Coalition of Tradefolk, Carson McCabe, Corrupt Qeynos Guards and The Freeport Militia.. if done the right way..(hits dont seem like much) make sure you do it with Slansin, not the original guy that is rarely there is a server is reset. If you can use the dude as a merchant, you do not want to do it (It will lower faction in Eurdin) If this happens make a mule enchanter (I think thats the same class as the guy who gives the quest) turn in your newbie note to get amible faction (so you can do the quest) and do it. This will make the merchant faction lowering guy poof and next time will be the guy you want to raise the non Erudin related factions.<br><br>Two things to note.. Paineel will REALLY hate you after killing Elial Brooks.. we start off kos anyway.. and our monk epic deals with Erudin.. and paineel is evil.. There is a possiblty of killing XXX? kolbolds or something in the warrens to get non kos to the guards of both citys, but you wont be able to go far at all. (Prob like 6000 to get non kos to paineel after killing brooks) The second thing.. Brooks is on a 6 min timer, it takes a long time for 60 kills. AND a guard patrolls along there, you gota kill brooks fast and get out of the way! You can stand on the very end of the dock to avoid the guard. <br><br>-<br><br>For the quests I mentioned zip over to allakhazam's for all you need (you prob already know that) everquest.allakhazam.com/<br><br>Okay one last thing.. the clerics in qeynos, its always a accomplisment to get non kos to the clerics in any city. You can feed Lashum Novine 2 gold, like the bards for faction hits. You will lower the blood sabers, so you cant go down under the city after this. Takes 1200 gold AKA 600 turn in.. yeah takes freeking forever! You will need to sneak and move each time to his side so your indiferent. (He will attack if your lower level, but at our level he will not - green)<br><br>Um.. that lil turd trumpy.. he likes honey mead.. if you give him 4 (I think) he will raise a number of factions, one is corupt.. however it will lower merchants and good guards. But! look at what they are already.. ally? amnible? Who cares if they balance out to indiferent as long as you get non kos to thoes mean evil guards.<br><br>If you are able to do monk quests, doing the lowest level one, from store bought material, is a super quick way to get faction up. You can get the wolf form so your able to do the quest, then do it like 50-80 times.. when you loose the wolf you will still be at amnible or so. Also raises guard faction which you might of lowered on getting up their oposing faction through faster then normal means. <br><br>Nice guide I refer people to it all the time, even got a social so I dont mispell it.  <br><br>I probably missed a lot.. if you have any questions or comments by all means let me know, you were always one of my heros along my faction adventures =)<br><br>